<item>
            <title>[LU-9407] sanity-lfsck test_20b: MDS1 is not the expected &quot;completed&apos;&apos; </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9407</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Doug Oucharek &amp;lt;doug.s.oucharek@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/fa0f7094-2a24-11e7-b742-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/fa0f7094-2a24-11e7-b742-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_20b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;(4) MDS1 is not the expected &apos;completed&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Many of the tests in the sanity-lfsck set which followed this one failed.  I am assuming this first failure triggered all the others (so won&apos;t create any additional tickets).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please provide additional information about the failure here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity-lfsck 20b&lt;/p&gt;</description>
